    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-01T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-01T23:00:00-05:00" n="653"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2851</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spencer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-02T13:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 2, 11.88 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my cable September 23, 4 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d653fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_692">p. 692</ref>.</note> and
                    confirming conversation I had with Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs Monday,
                    Embassy received to-day memorandum from Foreign Office stating that Japanese
                    Government painfully shocked at information mass terrorism in Moscow, Petrograd.
                    It shares the profound sense of horror of the American Government and will
                    gladly join in protest as suggested against acts of sheer brutality.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spencer</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
